package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"os"
	"strings"
)

func main() {
	who := "World!"
	if len(os.Args) > 1 {
		who = strings.Join(os.Args[1:], " ")
	}
	fmt.Println("Hello", who)
}

#!/bin/bash

if [ "$#" -ne 1 ]; then
    echo "Usage: ./file.sh [filename]"
    exit 1
fi

if [ -f $1 ]; then
    echo "File $1 exists"
    if [ -w $1 ]; then
        echo "File $1 has write permission"
    fi
else
    echo "File $1 does not exist"
fi

exit 0
